<ContentPage
  title="Cookie Statement — LazyTools Sets No Cookies | LazyTools"
  description="LazyTools sets no cookies at all — no analytics cookies, no advertising, no tracking. Some tools save your preferences in your browser's own local storage, which never leaves your device. Here's exactly what that means."
  heading="Cookie Statement"
  updated="July 12, 2026"
>
  <p>
    <strong>LazyTools sets no cookies.</strong> None — not for analytics, not for advertising, not for tracking.
    We don't run any analytics service at all. Because no cookies are set, there is nothing for you to consent to
    and no cookie banner to click through.
  </p>

  <h2>What we use instead</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Local storage, kept locally.</strong> Some tools remember your preferences or saved data — Pomodoro settings, Kanban boards, a saved unit, whether you've rated a tool — using your browser's own local storage. This is <em>not</em> a cookie: it stays on your device, is never transmitted to us, and you can clear it any time via your browser settings.</li>
    <li><strong>Nothing else.</strong> No first-party or third-party cookies are placed by this site.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>What we don't use</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>No analytics cookies, and no analytics service of any kind.</li>
    <li>No advertising or marketing cookies.</li>
    <li>No cross-site tracking or identifiers that follow you around the web.</li>
    <li>No cookies tied to your tool usage — the content you process never reaches a server in the first place.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>A note on server logs</h2>
  <p>
    Loading any website means your browser makes a request to a server, and — like every host — ours keeps
    standard access logs (see the <a href="/privacy/">privacy policy</a>). That's ordinary web infrastructure,
    not a cookie and not something this site configures for tracking.
  </p>

  <h2>Questions</h2>
  <p>
    Every tool on this site works exactly the same with or without any browser storage, because the tools don't
    depend on it. Questions? <a href="/contact/">Contact us</a>.
  </p>
</ContentPage>
